article.headline: Pierson scores 29 points for Red Raiders
article.linkText: Pierson's hot streak continues in Texas Tech win
article.story:
LAWRENCE, Kan. (AP) -- Plenette Pierson had another big game for
No. 8 Texas Tech.

	   Pierson scored 29 points and had six rebounds to lead Tech over
Kansas 84-57 Saturday.

	   Pierson set a career high with 32 points earlier this week in an
84-50 win over Missouri.

	   "I think I am more comfortable," said Pierson, who shot
11-of-14 from the field. "It was a long week, and it is great for
us to get another win."

	   Texas Tech (18-2, 7-1 Big 12) forced 18 turnovers and converted
them into 25 points.

	  "It was big for us," Pierson said. "We are 7-1, and five of
those have been on the road. It is difficult to get wins on the
road."

	   Kansas (9-10, 2-6) struggled for much of the game, going 7-of-25
in the first half and shooting only 33 percent for the game.

	   Jia Perkins added 13 points for Tech.

	   Aquanita Burras led Kansas with 16 points and five rebounds. She
shot 10-for-10 from the line. They also received eight points and
eight rebounds from Tamara Ransburg.

	   "I was watching game film, and I saw so many things change for
this Kansas team," said Texas Tech coach Marsha Sharp, who needs
three wins for 500. "They are going to be a really good basketball
team."

	   Pierson had 21 first-half points, and Tech led 38-22 at the
break.
